The paper proposes a deep learning framework for classifying images of immature leukemic blasts and normal cells. This involves using a combination of Discrete Cosine Transform (DCT) domain features extracted via CNN and Optical Density (OD) space features to build a robust classifier. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image classification. Additionally, the use of deep learning and CNNs suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves experiments to validate the proposed classifier, which could place it in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of feature extraction and classification techniques suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
